  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Numeric Rating Pain Scale (NRPS)</measure>
    <time_frame>recorded for one week post-operatively</time_frame>
    <description>A scale from 0-10 is used for patients to record the amount of pain they are experiencing at a given time. Multiple questions are asked on a daily basis in a pain diary to report pain in the morning, at night, with movement, before and after pain medication.</description>
